\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Last night you ghosted me in the middle of a text convo; Arlo was sick and badly needed your attention. I knew the reason immediately. It was a perfectly legitimate reason. Still, I started to feel a little put off at the abrupt and uncommunicated disappearance. These days, when I start to feel anything unpleasant, I force myself stop and consider where exactly that feeling is coming from, and from there decide whether or not that feeling is worth communicating, or if its something I need to deal with myself.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The upset part of me was saying, you know, I bet 99% of people would take 5 seconds to send a quick brb/gotta-go update instead of just disappearing. The upset part of me was wondering, am I so far outside of her concern that even a basic courtesy doesn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t crack the shell? I\u8217\'92m not litigating this here, just explaining what was running through the co-dependent part of my mind.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The other part of my mind began down that route which you suggested in the skimpy clothes convo, the route that says: I if I *knew* that you really, really liked me, would I be upset about the sudden ghost? Or, is this moody feeling only a manifestation of an insecurity about how you feel about me? The answer to that was obvious: I would not be upset if I were confident of your affection. If I was 100% confident, a ghosting would only leave me wondering, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91I hope she and Arlo are alright\u8217\'92, and obviously not, \u8216\'91damn, where do I fit in here?\u8217\'92. So, I took a quick stock of whether or not anything you had done or said warranted that insecurity, and outside the offhand comment where you mentioned you were feeling distant from me, there wasn\u8217\'92t. So, I immediately chilled out, realized this was an insecurity of baby mike\u8217\'92s, not mine. Then I began to hope that you and Arlo were alright, and decided to rest up for the weekend. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Katherine 3}}